author: Richard Barley
title: What if the Emerging-Market Move Isn’t a Head Fake?
text:
Investors love trends they can latch on to; turning points are more difficult to navigate. So, while investors have welcomed a sudden bout of stabilization in emerging markets, it could still prove disruptive.
More upbeat sentiment last week gave a lift to developed-market asset prices and an even bigger one to beaten-down investments in emerging countries. Currencies have bounced: since the start of October, the Russian ruble has...
